The fate of Semele the daughter of Cadmus, can have no other foundation, than that her gallantries with a prince of the name of Jupiter, were no less fatal than those which are said to have happened her with the heathen deity. The infant, whom Jupiter took from her womb, and matun-ed in his thigh, is not the Bacchus who reigned in Egypt, of whom we shall have occasion to make mention. Semele was numbered amongst the gods, under the name of Thyone.
